metadata.title: Laughing at Boss Jokes
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - empty room, coffee in Wally's hand. Characters: Wally - 'Can I get a bonus if I laugh at your jokes during meetings?', Boss - [no text]. Panel 2: Boss - 'I already have sycophants to do that function for free. What would you add?'. Panel 3: Wally - 'I can blow coffee out of my nose.' (pointing to his nose with free hand), Boss - 'Good, good. I can work with that.' (chin in hand thinking pose)

metadata.title: Can't Use Personal Laptop
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - blondeTed sitting, boss standing. Characters: blondeTed - [no text] (leaning back tense expression, looking concerned), Boss - 'You're not allowed to use your personal computer for work.'. Panel 2: Boss - 'And your company laptop won't show up for another two weeks.'. Panel 3: blondeTed - 'So... What should I do all day?', Boss - 'Do you know what pantomime is?'.

metadata.title: Can't work remotely.
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - dilbert and boss walking through the office hallways to the coffeemachine, both holding their cup. Characters: Boss - [no text], Dilbert - 'Remind me why we can't work remotely.'. Panel 2: Boss - 'Well, the first reason is because casual contact in the workplace enhances employee communication.'. Dilbert - 'Really? Because it doesn't feel that way.'. Panel 3: Dilbert - 'It feels more like getting waterboarded by a continuous drip of useless interruptions.' (pinching eyes). Panel 4: Dilbert - 'This place is 50% oxygen and 50% complaining.' (grabbing coffee pot). Panel 5: Dilbert - 'I get tense when I hear footsteps approaching. I believe it takes years off my live.' (pouring coffee into his cup). Panel 6: Dilbert - 'I mean, it feels like a hostage situation, if I am being honest.'. Boss - 'And the second reason is because it is good for morale.' (grabbing pot that Dilbert had put back down into coffee machine).

metadata.title: Managers Hear 12 Words
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - sitting at a table with coffee. Characters: Wally - 'Remember, managers can only hear the first twelve words you speak. After that, they drift off.', Asok - [no text]. Panel 2: Wally - 'So you need to be brief, yet 100% complete, or your career is toast.'. Asok - 'The pressure is killing me!!!' (shouting and shaking). Panel 3: Asok - 'I... I... I...' (shaking and sweating), CEO - 'You have nine words left.' (crossed arms).

metadata.title: Management By Weather
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - sitting at table, coffee. Characters: Boss - 'I like to match my management practices to the weather.' Carol - [no text]. Panel 2: Boss - 'For example, if I need to deliver bad news, I wait for a sunny day so it doesn't sting as much.'. Panel 3: Carol - 'That's terrific, but can we get back to my annual performance review?' Boss - 'As soon as the clouds break.'

metadata.title: Inexperienced Fool
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - office, papers in hands. Characters: Boss - 'Run your numbers through the VSADD, and let's see if they turn upside down.' Asok - [no text]. Panel 2: Asok - 'VSADD? What is that?' Boss (off-screen) - 'Get out of my office, you inexperienced fool!' Panel 3: Asok - 'What was I supposed to do in that situation?' Wally - 'I usually pretend I didn't hear it.'

metadata.title: Spy On Corporate Nemesis
metadata.content: Panel 1: Setting - office, boss with coffee cup in hand. Characters: Boss - 'I need you to spy on my corporate nemesis and report back to me on what he's thinking.' Dilbert - [no text]. Panel 2: Dilbert - 'He thinks you're an unethical weasel with no redeeming qualities.' Boss - [no text]. Panel 3: Boss - 'You haven't spied on him yet.' Dilbert - 'I'm an excellent guesser.'
